comments: I enjoyed working on this experiment.
I found it a bit challenging to decide what percentage of population would qualify to make something true.

I feel like it took me a second to understand what this experiment was about. At first I was trying to reason based on the names of the animals and whether I thought they were real but then I started going with the percentages and it made a lot more sense.

Speech/writing should more frequently contain qualifying words like "all" and "many" and "some" etc.  This would prevent confusion that would result form making statements like "Luzaks like to cuddle" when only 11% were found to like to cuddle.
Wondering if they were real animals.
